        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 1:50PM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 149 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Manhattan, or near Frankfort, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Frankfort Square, Manhattan, Frankfort, Mokena, University Park,
Tinley Park, Park Forest, New Lenox, and Orland Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
